cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with conditional GANs for image translation and manipulation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel framework for learning attribute representations to condition the generator, which involves graph convolutional networks (cs.GR) and multi-task learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods in encoding high-order semantic information and dependencies, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed methods on face attribute manipulation datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
